- 'recent encounters' refers to the most recent access events, ordered by 'access_date' in descending order; 
- 'stories behind the encounters' refers to the details of each access event; 
- 'library items' refers to the items with unique barcodes; 
- 'who met them' refers to the full names of the users; 
- 'where they were kept' refers to the physical locations of the items, represented by location codes; 
- 'how they were met' refers to the type of access (e.g., view, check out, check in).
